description:
What do you do when you're ripped from the 21st century and thrown into the middle of one of the greatest - and most bloodthirsty - civilizations in human history? How do you survive a strange world of war, blood, sacrifice, and death?

Sacrifice is "about Aztecs, Time Travel, and Joy Division." - Rob Humphries.

Sacrifice is a mini-series (in six parts) created, written and self-published by Sam Humphries (Uncanny X-Force, Higher Earth, Our Love is Real, CBGB: The Comic Book) and illustrated by newcomer artist Dalton Rose. It follows a young adolescent with epilepsy, Hector, somehow winding up in the Aztec empire with knowledge of what will happen next to this civilization. While the Aztecs discuss whether to sacrifice Hector or use him as apprentice to a high priest, Hector has to make a decision whether to fight or not. Besides, what's Hector connection to the Aztecs anyway and will he rewrite history?

Collected in Sacrifice by Dark Horse.
name: Sacrifice

deck: A Doctor Who Annual by any other name, published by Marvel UK from 1992 to 1996
description: From 1965 until 1986 World Distributors held a license to produce Doctor Who Annuals. A few years after they let it lapse Marvel UK, who had long held the license for Doctor Who Magazine, took up the annual license, though they changed the name to the Doctor Who Yearbook to distinguish it from World Distributors' version. Each volume included features, comic strips and text stories. Marvel published five yearbooks between 1991 and 1995 (the 1992 to 1996 ones, dating a year ahead as was normal for British annuals). There would be a decade-long gap between the final Yearbook and the next Doctor Who Annual, this time published by Marvel UK's successor to the Doctor Who Magazine license, Panini.
name: Doctor Who Yearbook

description: Sci-fi one shot.

deck: World Distributors' long running Doctor Who Annual
description: In 1965 World Distributors licensed the rights to produce annuals based on the BBC's Doctor Who TV show. They would subsequently publish 20 annuals through until 1985 (Doctor Who Annuals 1966 to 1986, dating a year ahead as was normal for British annuals, and skipping only 1972), plus four Dalek Annuals in the 1970s, a K9 Annual in 1983, and a 1966 novella, Invasion from Space. A few years after they let the license lapse, Marvel UK picked it up and began publishing Doctor Who Yearbooks.
name: Doctor Who Annual

description: A new series of Doctor Who Annuals launched to tie in with the revived TV show. Initially published by Panini, current holder of the license to publish Doctor Who Magazine, they follow the format of the past Doctor Who Annuals and Yearbooks, with a mixture of features, text stories and comic strips, although from the second (2007) annual on, much of the story content was split off into a separate volume, Panini's Doctor Who Storybook series, leaving the annuals, now published by BBC Books, to concentrate more on games, activities and puzzles aimed at younger readers.
name: Doctor Who Annual

description:
KRANBURN BACKGROUND:

95.5% of humanity is dead. All that is left are settlements dotted throughout the landscape. In this kill or be killed environment the peaceful settlement of Kranburn cannot continue to take the passive route when might equals right and a mad dictator to the north has every intention of destroying them.

Kranburn is a story seen mostly from the point of view of Brand, a resident of Kranburn.

In 1992 a plague ravaged the world. Totally unprepared for the fast spreading illness mankind was made nearly extinct, with only .5% being immune and seeing 1993. Fast forward to the year 2015 and life has stuttered but continued, mostly in the form of strongholds and settlements. This story follows the settlement of Kranburn, a small town built on what was once the rooftop car park of an old shopping centre.

The published version of the highly regarded web comic series as can be found here. It can be alternatively be found in most of the many Melbourne based Comic Book stores, or for overseas readers interested can be bought online through the publisher FEC Comics.
name: Kranburn
